{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_017P4UxtgKjcqnSDkzuhzrSs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. Let me create the wallet funding helper. I need to:\n\n1. Create deterministic keypairs (using `Keypair.fromSeed()` with fixed seeds)\n2. Create an airdrop+confirm helper function\n3. Export everything for use in tests\n\nThe file should go at `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts`.\n\nKey design:\n- Two deterministic keypairs: PLAYER_A and PLAYER_B (from fixed 32-byte seeds)\n- `fundWallet(connection, publicKey, lamports)` — airdrop + confirmTransaction\n\n\n- `fundTestWallets(rpcUrl)` — convenience function that funds both players with 10 SOL each\n\nI should verify the Playwright setup can access `@solana/web3.js` since it's a dependency of the platform app and Playwright runs in Node.js. The e2e tests have their own TypeScript config that Playwright handles, so importing the library directly should work fine.\n\nWriting the helper file...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2346,"cache_read_input_tokens":49673,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2346},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"248c4ef4-b3ae-4077-b882-1fe8d3113a11","uuid":"c6182c7e-ff3c-4fe7-b1d4-27c13e9371af"}
